initial_story:
The Prince and Princess of Wales have released a new photo of their children Prince George, Princess Charlotte and Prince Louis, to celebrate Christmas.

In the black and white photo, which was taken by Josh Shinner, the children are seen sitting on a wooden bench.

Shinner also took the image used on the family's Christmas card this year.

The couple posted the picture on social media, writing "Wishing everyone a very Merry Christmas, from our family to yours! W & C".

In their Christmas card image, released earlier this month, the family was seen together in another black and white photo arranged around Princess Charlotte sitting on a chair.

They were all wearing white shirts, with Catherine, Princess of Wales, and daughter Charlotte, eight, wearing jeans, while the Prince of Wales wore black trousers along with son Prince George, 10, and Prince Louis, five, who was in shorts.

In the picture the couple shared on Christmas Day, the three children seem to be wearing the same clothes and shoes as in the Christmas card image.

The family is at Sandringham in Norfolk for Christmas Day and is attending a church service in the morning.

Catherine hosted the Together At Christmas carol service event at Westminster Abbey, which was broadcast on Christmas Eve.

The famous rockstars, Bruno Mars and Ed Sheeran, have released a new photo to celebrate their latest music tour. In the black and white image, taken by celebrity photographer, Anna Taylor, the musicians are seen sitting on a vintage stage trunk. The image was also used on the promotional materials for their tour.

The duo posted the picture on social media, writing "Huge thank you to our fans for an incredible year! We hope you enjoy our new music and memories made on the road. Wishes from Bruno and Ed".

In their promotional image, released earlier this month, the pair was seen posing together in another black and white photo, with their music instruments. They were all wearing sleek black attire, including Bruno's iconic sunglasses.

In the picture the duo shared on social media, they seemed to be wearing the same outfits as in the promotional image.

After their last show in Los Angeles, they're taking a well-deserved break and will be ringing in the new year with a party in Hawaii. But before that, they've invited their fans to participate in their charity event, a special concert at Central Park Zoo, set to take place on New Year's Eve.

The beloved ballerinas, Misty Copeland and Misty Lown, have shared a stunning photograph on social media to celebrate their latest dance tour. In the elegantly captured shot, the pair are seen posed on a ornate mirrored vanity, with their elaborate costumes reflecting their radiance. The photograph was taken by renowned dance photographer, Chris Nash, and will be featured on promotional materials for their upcoming tour.

Misty and Misty captioned their post: "Gratitude to our loyal supporters for an enchanting year! We hope our new dance routines and cherished memories from the stage will ignite inspiration in you. Wishes from us, Misty & Misty".

In another promotional snapshot, the dancers were seen dancing together in a grand, ornate ballroom, surrounded by lavish chandeliers and gilded frames. They both wore ornate tutus and their tutu caps. In their social media posting, they resembled similar attire to that of their earlier promotional photo.

Following their final performance in New York, they will be embarking on a rejuvenating break, culminating in a lavish ball in St. Petersburg, Russia. But before that, they have extended an invitation to their fans to join them for their charity gala at the Russian National Museum of Fine Arts, scheduled for New Year's Eve.
